    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long staffs often having a pointed lower tip and topped by a knob or hook onto which was attached a gourd (pilgrim's gourd), a cloth tied into a sack, or other item. Used as an aid walking on pilgrimages; some were decorated with religious inscriptions and images.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079245/Catholic Encyclopedia [online] (2003-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bastone di notevole lunghezza che termina generalmente con un puntale e, all'estremità opposta, con un pomo o un gancio per appendere il fazzoletto e la fiasca (fiasca di pellegrinaggio). Alcuni sono ornati con scene e iscrizioni religiose</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Italian</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Long bâton doté à sa base d'une pointe et souvent terminé à son sommet par une boule ou un crochet, auquel étaient attachés une gourde (gourde de pèlerinage) et éventuellement un baluchon. Certains bâtons de pèlerin sont décorés de scènes religieuses et d'inscriptions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>French</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Bordón de notable largueza que termina generalmente con un regatón y en el extremo opuesto, con un pomo o un gancho para colgar el pañuelo y el frasco (frasco de peregrinaje). Algunos están adornados con escenas e inscripciones religiosas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Longo bastão com ponteira, com terminação superior em forma de pomo ou de gancho, a que se prende um lenço e a cabaça (cabaça de peregrino). Pode ser ornamentado com cenas e inscrições religiosas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000049836/Thesaurus del corredo ecclesiastico [online] (1999)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lange staven, met onderaan een punt en bovenaan een knop of haak, waaraan men een kalebasfles kan hangen, een knapzak of andere objecten. Pelgrims gebruiken ze als wandelstaf. Sommige zijn versierd met religieuze inscripties en afbeeldingen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
